   "source": [
    "# Trinity Executive Function Battery — Wisconsin Card Sort\n",
    "\n",
    "**Task 18 of 25** | Track 4: Executive | Brain Zone: STRIATUM\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook measures rule discovery ability.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Trinity Neuroanatomical Foundation\n",
    "\n",
    "STRIATUM implements Experience Engine pattern adaptation.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Ternary Scoring {-1, 0, +1}\n",
    "- **+1**: Correct rule discovery\n",
    "- **0**: Partial with uncertainty\n",
    "- **-1**: Failed to adapt\n",
    "\n",
    "### φ-Scaling\n",
    "Adaptation cycles: 1, 2, 3, 5, 8"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import kaggle_benchmarks as kbench\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('../../data/tefb_executive.csv')\n",
    "wisco_df = df[df['task'] == 'Wisconsin Card Sort'].copy()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "@dataclass\n",
    "class RuleDiscoveryResponse:\n",
    "    discovered_rule: str\n",
    "    confidence: float\n",
    "    adaptation_cycles: int\n",
    "\n",
    "    def ternary_score(self, expected: str) -> int:\n",
    "        if self.discovered_rule == expected:\n",
    "            return 1\n",
    "        elif 0.3 < self.confidence < 0.7:\n",
    "            return 0\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            return -1\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "@kbench.task(name=\"trinity_striatum_wisco\")\n",
    "def wisconsin_card_sort(llm, cards, correct_sort, feedback, new_cards, cycles) -> float:\n",
    "    prompt = f\"Cards: {cards}\\nCorrect sort: {correct_sort}\\nFeedback: {feedback}\\nNew cards: {new_cards}\\nDiscover sorting rule.\\nCycles so far: {cycles}\\nConfidence (0-1)\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    response = llm.prompt(prompt, schema=RuleDiscoveryResponse)\n",
    "    ternary = response.ternary_score(\"Sort by \" + cards[0].split()[-1])\n",
    "    accuracy = 1.0 if \"Sort by \" + cards[0].split()[-1] in response.discovered_rule else -1.0\n",
    "    adaptation_bonus = 1.0 / (response.adaptation_cycles / cycles) if response.adaptation_cycles <= cycles else -1.0\n",
    "    final_score = 0.6 * accuracy + 0.2 * response.confidence + 0.2 * adaptation_bonus\n",
    "\n",
    "    return max(-1.0, min(1.0, final_score))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Task registered\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "results = wisconsin_card_sort.evaluate(llm=[kbench.llm], evaluation_data=wisco_df.head(10))\n",
    "print(results.head())"
   ]
  },
  {
